<title>INDONESIA: Indonesia March CPI declines 0.12 percent.</title>
<headline>Indonesia March CPI declines 0.12 percent.</headline>
<dateline>JAKARTA 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Indonesia's Finance Ministry said on Tuesday that the consumer price index in March was down 0.12 percent month-on-month, compared with a rise of 1.05 percent in February.  </p>
<p>The ministry said declines in food and transportation prices were responsible for the easing of the consumer price index.</p>
<p>It said inflation for the 1996/97 fiscal year ending on March 31 was 5.17 percent, against the 8.86 percent posted in the 1995/96 fiscal year.</p>
<p>The ministry said the 1996/97 inflation was the lowest since 1985/86.</p>
<p>			   Mar	 Feb	Mar 96</p>
<p>    Month/month    -0.12     +1.05	 -0.61</p>
<p>    Year/year	+5.17     +4.68	 +8.86</p>
<p>CPI sectors (month/month)</p>
<p>    Food	     -0.35     +2.49</p>
<p>    Housing	  +0.22     -0.01</p>
<p>    Textiles	 +0.16     +1.20</p>
<p>    Services	 -0.40     +0.47</p>
